===Motivation===

[https://github.com/ElementsProject/elements Elements], [https://github.com/Blockstream/gdk GDK] and [https://github.com/Blockstream/lwk LWK] ("Liquid reference wallets") currently enforce a wallet-side 546 sats dust limit, originally inherited from Bitcoin Core<ref>[https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/ee68b05f3d639b28b9d23b48324bc5f20ccfe49c/src/policy/policy.cpp#L36 Bitcoin Core Policy]</ref>. With ELIP 200<ref>[https://github.com/ElementsProject/ELIPs/blob/main/elip-0200.mediawiki ELIP 200]</ref> live on Liquid mainnet, network fees for Confidential Transactions dropped by ~10x, with <20 sats total for a single input, single output Confidential Transaction. The default dust limit of Liquid's reference wallet libraries should be lowered to reflect this and allow for micropayment use cases on Liquid.

==Design==

The dust limit for Confidential Transactions is not enforced at the network level<ref>[https://github.com/ElementsProject/elements/blob/master/src/policy/policy.cpp#L59 Elements Policy]</ref>, as transaction amounts are blinded. The GDK and LWK wallet libraries already offer settings to manually change the dust limit to a different arbitrary value. This proposal is about changing the default of this value for above-mentioned reference wallets from currently 546 sats to e.g. 55 (546/10) or 21 sats (a very prominent amount for tipping) and establishing a new lower default dust value for the Liquid ecosystem.

